 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Mon, 18 Jun 2007 12:04:23 +1000

fll-installer (0.0.14) unstable; urgency=low

  * modules/backend/system_services.bm: complete logic rewrite due to last
    changes. Runlevel configurations are no longer fully preserved as we did
    not copy the read only mount to the hdd, but the live system. SCan the
    installed init scripts, (re)configure them if they are in the service
    whitelist. We look up required update-rc.d command by analyzing the read
    only mount point runlevel configuration with fll_analyze_initscripts.
  * modules/backend/system_services.bm: no longer need to detect if various
    services were started, if they were started by fll-live-initscripts they
    were also configured/preserved wrt to sysvinit.
  * modules/backend/system_services.bm: remove aumix and modutils from service
    whitelist array.
  * modules/backend/system_services.bm: fix test to see if ssh requires
    preconfiguration.
  * Depend on rsync and fll-live-initscripts.

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Mon, 18 Jun 2007 02:34:45 +1000

fll-installer (0.0.13) unstable; urgency=low

  [ Kel Modderman ]
  * modules/backend/copy2HD.bm: rewrite the function that does the live -> hd
    copy. Use rsync with an exclude file. Copy the live filesystem, not just
    the read only mount point.
  * data/exclusion_list: add this list for input to rsync in copy2HD.
  * modules/backend/fix_etc_on_HD.bm: no longer special handle /tmp
  * modules/backend/convert_live2HD.bm: no longer call functions copy_etc2HD,
    copy_home2HD or system_create_modules.
  * modules/backend/system_findchanged.bm: removed
  * modules/backend/system_create_modules.bm: removed
  * modules/backend/copy_etc2HD.bm: removed
  * modules/backend/copy_home2HD.bm: removed
  * modules/backend/fix_home_on_HD.bm:
    - mv $live_user $new_user on target filesystem
    - no longer manually rm user tmp files, they are excluded at rsync time
  * modules/backend/fix_locales_on_HD.bm: cleanups
    - update Needs: header for TARGET_MNT_POINT and USER_NAME
    - use /usr/bin/env -i to ensure clean environment apart from FLL_LANG when
      calling /etc/init.d/fll-locales with argument of "localize".
    - update .kde/share/config/kxkbrc for installed user based on new
      KDEKEYBOARDS.
    - fix typo, s/fll_locales/fll-locales/
  * modules/backend/fix_home_on_HD.bm: many cleanups
    - remove /root/.hushlogin that may have been put there by fll-rootsh
    - same for /home/$user/.hushlogin
    - put all file removals in a for loop
    - put all sudo removals in a for loop
    - don't clobber ~/.bashrc, just use sed to make sudo vanish

  [ Joaquim Boura ]
  * modules/backend/progress.bm: code it's already in the initialization
  * modules/backend/fix_etc_on_HD.bm: update-menu was already gone
  * modules/backend/prpareHD.bm: typo in file name fixed

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Sun, 17 Jun 2007 23:27:03 +1000

